The existing tests in `resolve.test.ts` that use `if (process.platform === "win32")` branches should be cleaned up. Once `test/cross-platform.test.ts` has full coverage of both templates, the platform-branching tests in `resolve.test.ts` can be simplified to just assert on the host platform's result (no branching) since the cross-platform correctness is now proven by the new file. The sudo lookup tests that run real system commands can stay or be replaced by equivalent mocked variants in the new file — both can coexist, with the real-command tests acting as integration smoke tests.

